      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Probability of Drawing the Q Tile: Scrabble Math Explained</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-14">June 14, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>7 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔍</span> Solver</a> <a href="/activities/#quiz" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🎯</span> Quiz</a> <a href="/activities/#anagram" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔀</span> Anagram</a> <a href="/activities/#rack" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🎲</span> Rack</a> <a href="/activities/#wotd" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">📖</span> WOTD</a> <a href="/sixty-seconds/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">⏱️</span> 60s</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        The Q tile is both the most feared and most rewarding tile in Scrabble. Worth 10 points but dependent on U, it creates a unique mathematical puzzle: what are the actual odds of drawing it, and when should you worry? Let's break down the exact probabilities at every stage of the game.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Opening Draw Probability</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">1/100</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Q tiles in bag</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">7</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Tiles drawn</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">7%</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Probability</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">1 in 14</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Games with Q first</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>The math is straightforward: with 1 Q in 100 tiles and 7 drawn, the probability of getting Q is approximately 7%. This means roughly 1 in every 14 games, you'll face Q on your very first rack.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 The Combined Q+U Draw</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Drawing Q <span class="text-white font-medium">and</span> U together in your opening 7 tiles has a probability of about <span class="text-white font-medium">2.8%</span> (1 in 36 games). That means in 60% of games where you draw Q first, you <em>won't</em> have U to go with it. Knowing Q-without-U words is essential.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Mid-Game Probabilities: As the Bag Shrinks</h2>
